column1: SDG 16.1 Significantly reduce all forms of violence and related death rates everywhere
Definition: Number of unlawful deaths inflicted upon a person with the intent to cause death or serious injury, expressed per 100,000 people.
Source: UNODC (United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime) (2020). DATAUNODC. https://dataunodc.un.org. Accessed 21 July 2020.

column2: Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development

column1: a: Data refer to the most recent year available during the period specified.
